cs.SE, cs.HC, cs.CV, cs.PL, cs.SD

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on automated support for documenting changes made to mobile apps, which is a key aspect of software engineering. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also likely as the paper deals with changes to the graphical user interface (GUI) of mobile apps, which is a key aspect of HCI. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is another likely category as the paper leverages computer vision techniques to detect GUI changes. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper deals with changes made to the code of mobile apps. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is a less likely category as the paper does not deal with sound or audio in any way.
